		"name": "Weather Consumer API Template",
		"description": "## Notes:\n\nFor AddMetric Endpoint ([http://localhost:8080/metrics](http://localhost:8080/metrics)):\n\n- sensorID should not be null\n    \n- timestamp should be in **ISO 8601 UTC** format (ending in `Z`)\n    \n\nFor Query Endpoint ([http://localhost:8080/metrics/query](http://localhost:8080/metrics/query))\n\n- `sensorIds`: `[]` means **all sensors**.\n    \n- `startDate` and `endDate` must be in **ISO 8601 UTC** format (ending in `Z`).\n    \n- Supported metrics: `\"temperature\"` and `\"humidity\"` (or both).\n    \n- Supported statistics: `\"avg\"`, `\"min\"`, `\"max\"`, `\"sum\"`. Notes:\n    - `sensorIds`: `[]` means **all sensors**.\n        \n    - `startDate` and `endDate` must be in **ISO 8601 UTC** format (ending in `Z`).\n        \n    - Supported metrics: `\"temperature\"` and `\"humidity\"` (or both).\n        \n    - Supported statistics: `\"avg\"`, `\"min\"`, `\"max\"`, `\"sum\"`.",
